SIMPLE: thirtieth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thirtieth
<hw>Thir"ti*eth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Thirty</er>: cf. AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦imac⟧tig⟦omac⟧⟦edh⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Next
in order after the twenty-ninth; the tenth after the twentieth; -- the
ordinal of <xex>thirty</xex>; <as>as, the <ex>thirtieth</ex> day of the
month</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Constituting or being one of thirty equal parts into
which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirtieth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thirtieth
<hw>Thir"ti*eth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quotient of a unit divided
by thirty; one of thirty equal parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirty</ent>⟦br⟧
